race.comment: Nice race with a few strong form lines. GOLDANE (6) has not appeared since her effortless victory on debut over 900m at Newcastle in January when well supported. Two recent trial wins have been outstanding. Looks ready to run a big race despite the long lay-off. DESI EMPEROR (2) led for home and gave a kick under his big weight before being overwhelmed close to home last start 1300m at Newcastle. Won't mind coming back in trip today and with 1.5kgs less after the claim can give backers a sight. POINT SCORE (4) quickened nicely to record an impressive win here at this trip last time out when second-up from a spell. Perfectly drawn and won't find this a great deal harder. Big chance again. TEQUILA BABY (5) last raced in April when an easy winner over 1100m at Hawkesbury, the only outing of that prep. Two trials in October should have her ready for a positive return. CORDINA (7) is back from a six-month break. Bolted in on debut to kick off last prep - should come to hand quickly.
